Andropogoneae Species

Michelle C. Stitzer

Anatherum virginicum

Photo by Donald Burk, licensed under CC-BY-NC 4.0

The assembly is haploid, and the genome is diploid. It has a haploid genome size of 900 Mb, and has 10 haploid chromosomes.

Metaphase chromosomes of Anatherum virginicumroot tips, scale bar 10 µm

Species herbarium records

Herbarium records of Anatherum virginicum from AuBuchon-Elder et al 2022 are plotted with black points, The sampled individual this genome was generated from is shown in a colored point. The green background shows the biogeographic ranges of all Andropogoneae species in AuBuchon-Elder et al 2022.

Dotplot of Anatherum virginicum vs. Paspalum vaginatum.

Like dotplots shown in Figure 3 of the main text, this shows syntenic blocks in Anatherum virginicum along the y-axis, vs P. vaginatum on the x-axis. As Anatherum virginicum is a diploid with a haploid, assembly, we expect 1 paths for any x-axis position.

Fractionation of Anatherum virginicum

Like plots shown in Figure 4 of the main text, this shows proportion of retained genes in Anatherum virginicum along the y-axis, vs P. vaginatum chromosomes on the x-axis. As Anatherum virginicum is a diploid with a haploid, assembly, we expect 1 lines, one for each subgenome.
